ers","2 fresh long green chillies, trimmed and cut into halves (optional)","1 tbsp garlic paste (see Tips)","1 tbsp ginger paste (see Tips)","40 g ghee (see Tips)","40 g canola oil","30 fresh curry leaves","800 g canned whole tomatoes","1 tbsp brown sugar","1 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","1 tsp salt"]},{"title":"Sabji","content":["170 g fresh baby spinach leaves","30 g cashews","2 fresh tomatoes, cut into quarters and deseeded (approx. 100 g)","200 g water","200 g potato, cut into pieces (2 cm)","100 g carrot, cut into pieces (1 cm)","200 g sweet potato, cut into pieces (2 cm)","100 g coconut cream","2 tsp garam masala (see Tips)","1 tsp salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","fresh long red chillies, cut into thin slices, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r136306","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-OumpzUBbSxo\/XZVRx7TWhVI\/AAAAAAAAdS8\/EaELOmk3dKQqATkhUAuSV2OGQE9GopZgACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_xYAQMYghuicmmygb.png","title":"Sabji (vegetable) curry","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.3 g","fat":"13.9 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"26.3 g","calories":"1136 kJ \/ 270 kcal"},"usefulItems":"snaplock bag, bowl, sealable container, freezeable containers, small bowl","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own garlic paste, ginger paste, ghee and garam masala, please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip.","Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Ever<\/em><em>yday Cookbook <\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","You can store the Everyday Indian curry paste in the refrigerator for up to 5 days or in the freezer for up to 6 weeks.","We served ours with pilau rice and cucumber raita, please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip, but you can serve with any side and condiment of your choice."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","50m","4 portions"]}